ping → Tests network path (is the server up? how fast is the connection?).
EXample : ping -c 4 google.com   # test internet connectivity
          ping 192.168.1.1       # check if your router is alive

curl → Tests application layer (HTTP/HTTPS)
Example: curl -I https://www.google.com   # show headers
         curl -o google.html https://www.google.com   # save page

wget → command-line tool for downloading files from the web.
Example: wget https://example.com/file.zip
